Detailed Description

ObitTimeFilter time filter class definition.

This class is derived from the Obit class. This class is for performing TimeFilter on memory resident data.

Creators and Destructors

An ObitTimeFilter can be created using newObitTimeFilter which allows specifying a name for the object, and the type, size and direction of the transform.

A copy of a pointer to an ObitTimeFilter should always be made using the ObitTimeFilterRef function which updates the reference count in the object. Then whenever freeing an ObitTimeFilter or changing a pointer, the function ObitTimeFilterUnref will decrement the reference count and destroy the object when the reference count hits 0. There is no explicit destructor.

Creators and Destructors

An ObitTimeFilter provides storage for one or more time series of floats in both the time and frequency (half complex) domains. The class also contains tools for transforming from one domain to the other and for applying a filter in the frequency domain. Typcal usage sequence is:
  • Create using newObitTimeFilter
  • fill time series data using #timeData ofloat pointer member
  • transform to frequency using ObitTimeFilter2Freq
  • apply filter using ObitTimeFilterFilter
  • transform back to time domain using ObitTimeFilter2Time
  • access filter time series using #timeData ofloat pointer member
  • unreference object using ObitTimeFilterUnref

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum obitTimeFilterType
 

enum for type of ObitTimeFilter filter type.

This specifies the type of filtering to be performed.

Enumeration values:
OBIT_TimeFilter_LowPass  Low pass filter.
OBIT_TimeFilter_HighPass  High pass filter.
OBIT_TimeFilter_NotchPass  Notch pass filter.
OBIT_TimeFilter_NotchBlock  Notch block filter.

void ObitTimeFilterDoFilter (  ObitTimeFilter *  in,
olong  seriesNo,
ObitTimeFilterType  type,
ofloat *  freq,
ObitErr *  err
) 
 

Public: Apply Filter to Frequency series with physical parameters.

Following Filters are supported:

  • OBIT_TimeFilter_LowPass - Zeroes frequencies above freq[0] (Hz)
  • OBIT_TimeFilter_HighPass - Zeroes frequencies below freq[0] (Hz)
  • OBIT_TimeFilter_NotchPass - Zeroes frequencies not in frequency range freq[0]->freq[1]
  • OBIT_TimeFilter_NotchBlock - Zeroes frequencies in frequency range freq[0]->freq[1]
Parameters:
in Object with TimeFilter structures.
seriesNo Which time/frequency series to apply to (0-rel), <0 => all
type Filter type to apply
freq Frequencies (Hz) for filter, meaning depends on type.
err Error stack

olong  seriesNo,
ObitTimeFilterType  type,
ofloat *  parms,
ObitErr *  err
) 
 

Public: Apply Filter to Frequency series.

Following Filters are supported:

  • OBIT_TimeFilter_LowPass - Zeroes frequencies above a fraction, parm[0], of the highest.
  • OBIT_TimeFilter_HighPass - Zeroes frequencies below a fraction, parm[0], of the highest.
  • OBIT_TimeFilter_NotchPass - Zeroes frequencies not in frequency range parm[0]->parm[1]
  • OBIT_TimeFilter_NotchBlock - Zeroes frequencies in frequency range parm[0]->parm[1]
Parameters:
